ENTRY       EC 1.1.1.252                Enzyme
NAME        tetrahydroxynaphthalene reductase
CLASS       Oxidoreductases;
            Acting on the CH-OH group of donors;
            With NAD+ or NADP+ as acceptor
SYSNAME     scytalone:NADP+ Delta5-oxidoreductase
REACTION    scytalone + NADP+ = 1,3,6,8-tetrahydroxynaphthalene + NADPH + H+ [RN:R02906]
ALL_REAC    R02906;
            (other) R03322
SUBSTRATE   scytalone [CPD:C00779];
            NADP+ [CPD:C00006]
PRODUCT     1,3,6,8-tetrahydroxynaphthalene [CPD:C04033];
            NADPH [CPD:C00005];
            H+ [CPD:C00080]
COMMENT     Reduces 1,3,6,8-tetrahydroxynaphthalene to scytalone and also reduces 1,3,8-trihydroxynaphthalene to vermelone. Involved with EC 4.2.1.94 scytalone dehydratase in the biosynthesis of melanin in pathogenic fungi.
HISTORY     EC 1.1.1.252 created 1992 as EC 1.3.1.50, transferred 1999 to EC 1.1.1.252
